The High Court in Pretoria has dismissed a bid to halt the reopening of schools. The challenge was brought by the One South Africa Movement, led by former DA leader Mmusi Maimane. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - The High Court in Pretoria has dismissed a bid to halt the reopening of schools. The challenge was brought by the One South Africa Movement, led by former DA leader Mmusi Maimane. The organisation says children should not continue going to class, as the country grapples with COVID-19. READ: Government gambling with children's lives: Maimane “It is a disappointing judgment because ultimately we fight to make sure all schools in the country are safe,” said Maimane. One South Africa Movement also wants the country to return to level 4 of the lockdown. Maimane added that the legal team will study the judgment before making a decision to appeal. - Coronavirus Hotline Number: 0800 029 999 from 8 am to 4 pm, Monday to Friday. Help protect your loved ones by sharing this official South African government COVID-19 service with your family, friends and community. Send HI to 0600 123 456 on WhatsApp. The NICD has another Clinician Hotline to improve #COVID19 communication and support for healthcare providers. The Clinician Hotline is 0800 11 1131, operating 24 hrs. The Public Hotline is 0800 029 999 also operating 24hrs.